The management of the Nigerian Stock Exchange (The NSE) during the week released the data of all stocks and share traded on the floor.  The record showed the top three equities namely FBN Holdings Plc, Zenith International Bank Plc and Fidelity Bank Plc by volume which accounted for 1.084 billion shares worth N17.852 billion in 7,074 deals, contributing 44.34% and 48.69% to the total equity turnover volume and value respectively. As result of above, the Financial Services Industry by volume led the activity chart with 2.044 billion shares valued at N26.330 billion traded in 16,788 deals; thus contributing 83.61% and 71.81% to the total equity turnover volume and value respectively. The Consumer Goods Industry followed with 168.973 million shares worth N8.111 billion in 4,927 deals. The Oil and Gas Industry’s turnover stood at 94.742 million shares worth N825.871 million in 1,641 deals. “The overall traded records showed total turnovers of 2.444 billion shares worth N36.665 billion in 26,712 deals were traded this week by investors on the floor of the Exchange in contrast to a total of 3.079 billion shares valued at N39.990 billion that exchanged hands last week in 23,086 deals. “Also traded during the week were a total of 1.889 million units of Exchange Traded Products (ETPs) valued at N10.512 million executed in 4 deals, compared with a total of 50,547 units valued at N4.593 million that was transacted last week in 12 deals “A total of 40,566 units of Federal Government Bonds valued at N44.313 million were traded this week in 29 deals, compared with a total of 6,574 units valued at N6.332 million transacted last week in 31 deals. “Twenty-five (25) equities appreciated in price during the week, lower than forty-five (45) of the previous week. Sixty (60) equities depreciated in price, higher than forty (40) equities of the previous week, while eighty-six (86) equities remained unchanged lower than eighty-seven (87) equities recorded in the preceding week. “The NSE All-Share Index at week depreciated by 2.85% to close at 41,935.93 and also Market Capitalization depreciated by 3.26% to close at N15.002 trillion respectively. Similarly, all other indices finished lower during the week with the exception of the NSE Insurance Index that appreciated by 0.25%